added.title: Baby Mouth
added.description: In order to find out about his family history, Robin takes a DNA test and discovers he's from Babylon.

added.title: The Cast
added.description: After breaking his leg, Robin is confined to his room and spies through a telescope.

added.title: Superhero Feud
added.description: Control Freak pits the Titans against the DC Superhero Girls to determine who is the best team in the universe.

added.title: The Road
added.description:
This episode takes place when the Bears are young cubs! The three bears, on their way through the desert, come upon a giant warehouse. It's like an Amazon fulfillment
center. The Bears try to make this box-filled paradise their home.

added.title: Tote Life
added.description: When a hipster grocery store clerk shames the Bears for asking for plastic grocery bags, the Bears realize that eco-friendly tote bags are their way of gaining acceptance amongst the progressive people of the Bay Area. But in their effort to gain popularity, the Bears let the culture of tote bags take over their lives.

added.title: Video Date
added.description: Panda is an avid e-dater, and when a lovely French woman matches with him and agrees to a video chat date. Panda and his brothers engineer the situation so Panda is able to show the best side of himself on the video chat, even if that side of him is completely exaggerated.

added.title: Chloe and Ice Bear
added.description: On a day out with just Ice Bear, Chloe realizes Ice Bear only runs errands for his brothers. Determined to show him a fun day in the city, Chloe promises to help Ice Bear have a good time, even if it means staying  in a museum after it closes.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: The Coach
added.description: The new coach at Elmore High stands up to Jamie. The new Coach witnesses Jamie bullying the other kids at lunch and steps in. Jamie is made to apologise, much to the amazement of the other kids. Gumball and Darwin worry about Jamie seeking revenge, especially when they see him sneaking into the back of Coach's car. They use their newly acquired gym skills to save the Coach from being bullied.

added.title: The Countdown
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are running late for school but need to arrive in time to avoid expulsion. Gumball and Darwin hit snooze too many times on their alarm clock and miss the school-bus. Miss Simian has threatened to expel them if they don't get to school on time. A mysterious clock appears showing exactly how long they have to get to school. When it looks like they aren't going to make it in time, they stop the clock which effects the space/time continuum.

added.title: The Colossus
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that it isn't wise to upset Hector, Elmore's resident Giant.

added.title: The Castle
added.description: When Mom is away "anything goes" and Dad's lack of rules soon attracts unwelcome houseguests.

added.title: Bomzobo Lives
added.description: During a routine trip to the DMV, Max takes a driving test to renew his license, but when a disguised Zombozo hijacks the role of instructor, Ben goes alien to stop the baddie and save their family road trip.

added.title: Assault on Pancake Palace
added.description: When Gwen enters a pancake eating contest at the world famous Pancake Palace, Ben finds the Bugg Bros. and must stop them before they obtain an endless supply of what fuels their creations: Pancake Palace pancakes.

added.title: Half-Sies
added.description: During a trip to the Lake of the Ozarks, Ben and Gwen squabble over Ben's unnecessary "half-birthday" celebration, but when Max gets word of a suspicious rockslide nearby, the cousins must put aside their differences if they are to rescue the trapped miners and uncover who is behind the manmade catastrophe before it's too late: the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Winter Break
added.description: Craig returns to the Creek after the long Winter Break only to find an empty wasteland and danger lurking in the snow.

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Wildernessa
added.description: An encounter with Wildernessa, guardian of the wilderness, inspires Kelsey to take up a cause.

added.title: Baby Brother Blues
added.description: When Beth is told that the impending arrival of a baby brother is about to ruin her life, she runs away to find a new family.

added.title: Space Codyty
added.description: Izzy, convinced that Cody is an alien, embarks on a journey through space to take him back home.

added.title: Slobbery
added.description: Apple and Onion have to get rid of Burger's roommate so Burger will help them.

added.title: Microwave's Dance Club
added.description: Apple and Onion need more room in a packed nightclub in order to bust their dance moves.

added.title: All Work and No Play
added.description: Apple and Onion build eye masks to sleep at work so they can have more time for fun.

added.title: The Never-Realm
added.description: The ninja arrive in the Never-Realm where they quickly find themselves overwhelmed. Luckily, they are taken in by a tribe of Ice Fishers who tell them Zane has been imprisoned by the evil Ice Emperor.

added.title: Fire Maker
added.description: The Ice Emperor learns of the ninja's arrival and sends his Blizzard Samurai warriors to destroy them and the villagers who sheltered them.

added.title: An Unlikely Ally
added.description: Lloyd runs afoul of the Ice Emperor's Blizzard Samurai but is rescued by a strange wolf with whom an unlikely friendship develops.

added.title: The Absolute Worst!
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, three criminals learn of the ninja's absence and stage a breakout of Kryptarium Prison, telling tall tales of how they were captured as they go.

added.title: The Message
added.description: Lloyd and his wolf-companion find a cave with the mech inside and a message from Zane that provides a clue to his fate.

added.title: Los Perdidos
added.description: When Vic joins a group of nighttime skaters called Los Perdidos, Val becomes suspicious of Vic's strange, new, vampire-like behavior.

added.title: Los Pajaros
added.description: When Valentino trades Huitzi's gifts for one of his own, the birds in town start to turn on him.

added.title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
added.description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club 2: Doll Island
added.description: In order to prove their bravery, V&V head to a haunted island to retrieve a special doll, but Charlene and Pineapple are intent on getting it first.

added.title: Claudus
added.description: Lion-O's dad King Claudus arrives on Third Earth, and turns out to be a big selfish jerk! Now Lion-O has to deal with his dad before he goes to war with the rest of the Thundercats.

added.title: Telethon
added.description: In order to save the Berbils, Cheetara uses her psychic powers to project a telethon into the brains of everyone on Third Earth.

added.title: Mall-Ra
added.description: Mumm-Ra builds a mall that's actually a giant labyrinth designed to trap the Thundercats forever. Too bad the Thundercats love the mall so much they could literally spend all eternity there.

added.title: Eclipsorr
added.description: Third Earth's sun is being blocked out by the Eclipsor Corporation, an amoral company that wants to sell its energy for a profit. The ThunderCats can't do anything about it because they don't have a spaceship, yet!

added.title: Wizz-Ra
added.description: The ThunderCats freak out when a spooky ghost dressed like a pharaoh appears in their mirrors! They quickly set about to getting rid of every reflective surface in their lair, because that ghost is scary and no one wants to talk to him!

added.title: Orangusnake Begins
added.description: Mao Mao goads Orangusnake and the Sky Pirates into becoming truly terrible villains worthy of a legendary hero such as himself.

added.title: Scared of Puppets
added.description: Mao Mao is scared of puppets.

added.title: The Perfect Couple
added.description: When Mao Mao accidentally breaks up the most perfect couple in Pure Heart Valley, he has to figure out how to get them back together.

added.title: Breezy
added.description: With a friendly bee named Breezy as his wingman, Finn decides to get back into the dating game.

added.title: Dentist
added.description: Finn's aching tooth leaves him with no other option but to go to the dentist.

added.title: Bad Little Boy
added.description: The princesses are sick and tired of Ice King's crazy Fionna & Cake stories, so Marceline stops by the Ice Kingdom to show him how it's done.

added.title: Blade of Grass
added.description: Finn and Jake decide it's time for Finn to get a new sword. Finn reluctantly buys a grass sword from a mysterious old man but the sword turns out to be cursed.

added.title: Betty
added.description: In Wizard City, a magic spell backfires and turns Ice King back into Simon.

added.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays Part 1
added.description: Unikitty and the gang secretly throw Master Frown the birthday of his dreams, but their efforts have lasting repercussions beyond Frown's special day.

added.title: The Birthday to End All Birthdays Part 2
added.description: Following the events of Master Frown's birthday, Unikitty and her friends form a resistance group to restore the Unikingdom.

added.title: Spoooooky Game
added.description: The gang's weekly board game night has been getting a little too competitive lately, so when Unikitty finds a spooky old board game that's clearly haunted, their desire to win gets turned upside down, but cursed or not, they'll be the first to the finish line!

added.title: Fire & Nice
added.description: When Master Frown causes Unikitty to have an angry outburst that gets a little too destructive, she wishes her Rage Kitty side wasn't part of her anymore. Thanks to a new Dr. Fox invention, she gets her wish: Rage Kitty and Nice Unikitty split apart into two! But with Unikitty now unable to get angry, she learns bottling up your anger is never a good thing.

added.title: Rock Friend
added.description: Unikitty discovers Puppycorn's only other friend is a boring old rock. Encouraged to "make more friends," Puppycorn just can't find someone he clicks with, until he takes her advice and decides to literally make a new friend out of the best parts of his friends. This won't go well.

added.title: Lost and Found
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby go get a wallet.

added.title: Fries Night
added.description: Benson wants some french fries to overcome his depression.

added.title: Can You Ear Me Now?
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby offend some people.

added.title: Kill 'Em with Kindness
added.description: Pops wants to be friends with someone.

added.title: Cheer Up Pops
added.description: The guys want to cheer up Pops.

added.title: El silencioso
added.description: Mientras que Lloyd y Harumi se aventuran a lo profundo de "Primeval's Eye" en busca de la tercer máscara Oni, los ninja tratan de arreglar al Bounty y hacer un descubrimiento sorprendente.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: The Quiet One
added.description: As Lloyd and Harumi venture deep into Primeval's Eye in search of the third Oni Mask, the ninja attempt to fix the Bounty and make a startling discovery.

added.title: Juego de mascaras
added.description: Mientras Lloyd y Harumi buscan el templo Oni para la última máscara, los ninjas son tomados como rehenes y descubren que verdaderas intensiones de la Princesa Harumi.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Game of Masks
added.description: As Lloyd and Harumi search the Oni Temple for the last mask, the ninja are taken hostage and discover Princess Harumi's true intentions.

added.title: Terror llegando
added.description: Los ninjas recurren al comisionado de la policía de Ninjago en un esfuerzo por ayudar a salvar a Lloyd y frustrar los esfuerzos de Harumi de resucitar al malvado Lord Garmadon.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Dread on Arrival
added.description: The ninja appeal to the police commissioner of Ninjago in an effort to help save Lloyd and thwart Harumi's efforts to resurrect the evil Lord Garmadon.

added.title: El verdadero potencial
added.description: Justo cuando los ninjas piensan que han salvado el día, Lord Garmadon regresa a Ninjago, y libera a Harumi, quien lo anima a "alcanzar su verdadero potencial" conquistando lo único que siempre se interpuso en su camino, su hijo, Lloyd.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: True Potential
added.description: Just when the Ninja think they have saved the day, Lord Garmadon returns to Ninjago, and frees Harumi, who encourages him to "achieve his true potential" by conquering the one thing that has always stood in his way, his son, Lloyd.

added.title: Ninjago chico, problemas grandes
added.description: Los ninjas corres a salvar a Lloyd. Un Lord Garmadon más poderoso que nunca, crea una enorme estatua para ayudarlo a gobernar Ninjago y a derrotar a los ninjas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Big Trouble, Little NinjaGo
added.description: The ninja race to save Lloyd, as a more powerful-than-ever Lord Garmadon creates an enormous Colossi to help him rule Ninjago and defeat the ninja.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: Trouble Clef
added.description: When Morbucks realizes that The Powerpuff Girls see her as a villain and not a friend, she sets out to turn the town against them.

added.title: Benwolf
added.description: In New Mexico, Max stops to visit an old friend, who's a Navajo Chief. Suddenly, a powerful storm comes out of nowhere. And behind bolts of purple lightning, a Navajo werewolf appears. As Ben battles the werewolf, he appears to be bitten and turns into Benwolf.

added.title: Battle for Cybertron IV Part 1
added.description: Bee and Cheetor find new allies in the depths of Cybertron, Windblade, Wheeljack and Teletraan-X battle Bludgeon for control of Vector Sigma, and the Decepticons reveal their superior weaponry on the battlefield.

added.title: Monster Weather
added.description: Max takes the kids to a drought stricken Chicago to see his favorite golden oldie band perform at a huge music festival. Once there, our heroes cross paths with a deranged weatherman.

added.title: Battle for Cybertron IV Part 2
added.description: With Vector Sigma destroyed, Megatron and Shockwave make a desperate attempt to destroy the Allspark.

added.title: The Loop Part 1
added.description: It's a beautiful day on Cybertron and only Hot Rod doesn't seem to be enjoying the festive Parade of Metals.

added.title: The Loop Part 2
added.description: After escaping The Loop, Hot Rod, Clobber and Perceptor must stay one step ahead of their terrifying pursuers.

added.title: The Dead End Part 1
added.description: When Clobber enters the Deception Loop to rescue Lockdown, she attracts the attention of a different Decepticon instead.

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Kart
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls compete in a race against some of their most vicious villains to win whatever is in the Mayor's mysterious box of mystery.

added.title: The Dead End Part 2
added.description: Hot Rod and Clobber attempt to convince a disoriented and distrustful Dead End to join them in their fight against the Quintessons.

added.title: The Spoon
added.description: A crash landing sends Townsville over the edge.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Dash/The Final Stage
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Dash: With Dan and Ajit eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition, the remaining Awesome Brawlers - Shun, Wynton, Lia and Lightning race to complete the second stage of the competition. In order to make it to the final stage, the gang will have to pull together to defeat some tough competition./The Final Stage: It's the final stage of the Bakugan Battle League Tokyo Edition! The remaining Awesome Brawlers are ready to go, but just as the final round begins, the competitors are surprised with some unwelcome guests.

added.title: The Tokyo Catastrophe/Bakugan Battle League Finale
added.description: The Tokyo Catastrophe: Haavik has highjacked the Bakugan Battle league - Tokyo Edition! He's been using the tournament as a platform for his sinister plot to bring chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo./Bakugan Battle League Finale: Haavik unleashes an army of unruly Bakugan to bring his own brand of chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo. It's all hands-on-deck to stop the invasion, and foil Haavik's plot.

added.title: Champion of the Universe, Dan!/Operation Babysitter
added.description: Champion of the Universe, Dan!: Dan starts "sleep brawling", rolling out Drago causing damage and confusion while he's fast asleep. With the help of a "sleep expert", Ajit attempts to stop Dan and put his "sleep brawling" to rest once and for all./Operation Babysitter: Ajit lands a job babysitting a rambunctious toddler - Aiden. Having no experience with kids, Ajit recruits Wynton to help him out. Things get a little out of hand when Aiden rolls out - Krakelious. Now, Ajit and Wynton have a tiny Baku-brawler on their hands, with no way to stop him!

added.title: Beastie Team Battle/Ajit and Lia
added.description: Beastie Team Battle: China Riot is on the lookout for a partner to team up with in the new Bakugan battle team tournament being held in Los Volmos. Riot may have only been after a brawling partner, but ends up with a new friend./Ajit and Lia: Lia knows the story of where Ajit found his Golden Baku-balls, but no one knows "how" he's able to partner with Golden Bakugan. To get the inside scoop, Lia tags along with Ajit at his new job as a security guard at the local Museum.

added.title: Once More into the Maze/Grandpas in the Wild
added.description: Once More into the Maze: Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett were spotted at the ruins where the great core cell is housed! Alarmed by the report from Benton Dusk, the Awesome Brawlers head to the Yucatan Peninsula to investigate./Grandpas in the Wild: During an all-out brawl with Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, the Awesome Brawlers are hit with an attack that sends everyone spiraling to various parts of the maze. Split up from the rest of the gang, Wynton and Lightning find themselves in a strange unfamiliar part of the maze. While trying to get their bearings, they discover some new golden allies.

added.title: Bombazobo Vive
added.description: Durante un viaje de rutina al DMV, Max toma un examen de manejo para renovar su licencia. Pero cuando Zombozo, disfrazado, se apropia del papel del instructor, Ben se convierte en alienígena para detener al malvado y salvar el viaje familiar.

added.title: Ataque en el Palacio de los Panqueques
added.description: Cuando Gwen se inscribe en un concurso de comer panqueques en el mundialmente famoso Palacio de los Panqueques, Ben encuentra a los Bugg Bros. y debe detenerlos antes de que puedan obtener una provisión infinita del elemento que les da vida a sus creaciones: los panqueques del Palacio del Panqueque.

added.title: A Media
added.description: Durante un viaje al Lago de los Ozarks, Ben y Gwen discuten sobre la innecesaria celebración de "medio cumpleaños" de Ben. Pero cuando Max se entera de un sospechoso desprendimiento de rocas cercano, los primos deben dejar de lado sus diferencias si quieren rescatar a los mineros atrapados y revelar quién está detrás de la catástrofe producida por el hombre antes de que sea demasiado tarde: los hermanos Bugg.

added.title: Juego tenebroso
added.description: Últimamente, la noche semanal de juegos de mesa de la banda se volvió demasiado competitiva, así que cuando Unikitty encuentra un viejo y espeluznante juego de mesa que claramente está embrujado, los deseos de ganar del grupo quedan dados vuelta, pero con o sin embrujo, iquieren ser los primeros en cruzar la línea de llegada!

added.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
added.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.

added.title: Quintos Quinces
added.description: Victor y Valentino quieren ir a la fiesta en la piscina de un amigo el mismo día que la fiesta de quince años de su abuela, así que usan una flauta mágica que les permite teletransportarse y asistir a ambas al mismo tiempo.

added.title: El Libro Final
added.description: El último libro de fantasía de la serie favorita de Kelsey desaparece de la biblioteca. Por eso, Craig decide ayudarla a resolver el misterio de quién se lo llevó.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Demasiados Tesoros
added.description: Con la esperanza de reparar su fuerte, Craig consigue la ayuda de Los Veloces Diez para llevarlos hasta la legendaria pila de basura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Moustache Cream
added.description: When UG and the gang are in a rush to purchase some emergency moustache cream, they face a formidable foe: Mart Mart.

added.title: Fuego y Hielo
added.description: Cuando Master Frown le provoca a Unikitty un ataque de ira que se vuelve demasiado destructivo, ella desea que su faceta de Rage Kitty ya no sea parte de ella. Gracias a un nuevo invento de la Dra. Fox, el E-MoteTV, la princesa consigue su deseo: iRage Kitty y Nice Unikitty se dividen en dos! Pero ahora que Unikitty es incapaz de enfadarse, aprende que reprimir la ira nunca es algo bueno.

added.title: Salvajessa
added.description: Un encuentro con Salvajessa, guardiana de la naturaleza, inspira a Kelsey a dedicarse a una causa.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Amigo roca
added.description: Unikitty descubre que el único otro amigo de Puppycorn es una roca vieja y aburrida. Incentivado a ""hacer más amigos"", Puppycorn no puede encontrar a alguien con quien sienta afinidad, hasta que sigue el consejo de Unikitty y decide literalmente hacer un nuevo amigo con las mejores partes de sus amigos. Esto no irá bien.

added.title: Mi Papa Puede Vencer a Tu Papa
added.description: Cuando un bravucón dice que su papá puede darle una paliza a la mamá de K.O., nuestro héroe acepta con alegría el desafío en nombre de Carol.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Iced Out
added.description: Madcap's latest creation, the Ice Crusher, puts the whole city in a deep freeze, forcing Axel and the team to face him in a game of high-stakes hockey or risk slip-sliding into another ice age!

added.title: My Dad Can Beat up Your Dad
added.description: When a bully says his dad can beat up KO's mom, KO gladly accepts the challenge on Carol's behalf.

added.title: Dollar Hunt
added.description: Clarence hosts a fun "dollar hunt" game to meet new friends. But things go awry when Clarence accidentally buries the money his Mom gave him to buy refreshments for her book club meeting.

added.title: Gathering Dark
added.description: Axel must help Bearbarian overcome his secret fear of the dark to stop Dynamo from stealing his ride.

added.title: The Wrinklegruff Gals
added.description: Sick of being the tiniest kids at their new school, the girls convince Professor Utonium to create a potion to make them older! Unfortunately, when they take too much, they become senior citizens and a prime target for Mojo Jojo!

added.title: Locked Out
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa gets locked out of his RV and accidentally sets off the security system, it's up to him and his friends to disarm it before it destroys them.

added.title: Jorts
added.description: When Mr. Gus gets stuck in an embarrassingly super tight pair of jorts, he has to somehow get out of them in order to save his friends.

added.title: Dream Boat
added.description: Sumo devotes himself to the Sisyphean task of building a boat, defying the expectations of everyone in his life, including himself.

added.title: El Reino del Jamas
added.description: Los ninja llegan al Never-Realm donde rápidamente se sienten abrumados. Afortunadamente, son recibidos por una tribu de pescadores de hielo que les dicen que Zane ha sido encarcelado por el malvado Emperador de hielo.

added.title: El Camino
added.description: iEste episodio transcurre cuando los Osos son cachorritos! Los tres Osos, en su viaje por el desierto, se topan con un depósito gigante. Los Osos tratan de convertir este paraíso repleto de cajas en su hogar.

added.title: Vida Ecologica
added.description: Cuando un vendedor moderno en un almacén avergüenza a los Osos por pedir bolsas de plástico, los Osos se dan cuenta de que las bolsas de tela ecológicas son su forma de lograr aceptación entre las personas progresistas del Área de la Bahía. Pero en su esfuerzo por conseguir popularidad, los Osos dejan que la cultura (y la cantidad) de bolsas de tela se apodere de sus vidas.

added.title: Video Cita
added.description: Panda es un ávido salidor de citas por Internet, y cuando una adorable mujer francesa coincide con él y accede a tener una cita virtual con video, Panda y sus hermanos manejan la situación para poder mostrar su mejor perfil en el video, aunque ese perfil sea absolutamente exagerado.

added.title: Leg Wrestler
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus argue over what show to watch on TV, Pizza Steve has the perfect way to solve their dilemma: Leg wrestling battle!

added.title: Chloe Y Polar
added.description: Un día, Chloe sale sola a pasear con Polar y se da cuenta de que Polar se la pasa haciéndoles recados a sus hermanos. Decidida a mostrarle cómo pasarla bien en la ciudad, Chloe promete ayudar a que Polar se divierta... Aunque eso signifique quedarse dentro de un museo después de la hora de cierre.

added.title: El Ultimo robo
added.description: K.O. decide ayudar a Ginger a redescrubrir sus tiempos de gloria.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: One Last Score
added.description: KO decides to help Ginger recapture her glory days.

added.title: Hibernacion
added.description: Por ser un grupo urbano, los Osos jamás escucharon hablar de la idea de hibernar, hasta que Chloe les cuenta al respecto. Pardo, a quien le encanta la idea de comer mucho y luego dormir todo lo que se le dé la gana, se entrega a la hibernación sin pensarlo. Pero está tan entusiasmado con la idea de hibernar... que no se puede dormir.

added.title: Road Trippin'
added.description: Realizing her and the Professor don't have much in common, Bubbles schedules a road trip with just the two of them.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: Tenemos que vigilar
added.description: K.O. se une al Sr. Gar en una operación de vigilancia.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Let's Have a Stakeout
added.description: KO joins Mr. Gar on a stakeout.

added.title: T.G.I.S
added.description: The Secret Saturdays come to Bellwood to investigate a rash of chupacabra attacks.

added.title: Goose Chase
added.description: While at the park, Clarence happily feeds some birds his sandwich, imagining himself as their king. He has a great time until one persistent goose will not leave him alone!

added.title: All Good in the Wood
added.description: When Suna and Ashley's science project turns into a hungry blob monster, Mega Man must team up with Wood Man to shut down the experiment gone wrong before it devours the city!

added.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
added.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

added.title: El Club de Los Solitarios 2, La Isla de las Munecas
added.description: Para probar su valentía, Victor y Valentino se dirigen a una isla embrujada para recuperar una muñeca especial, pero Charlene y Piña están decididos a obtenerla antes que ellos.

added.title: Fire Man in the Hole
